<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36208e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36208e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36208e"> 208(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Endowments</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Mormonism.]</font> She was next given the sacred drawers, &ldquo;like the child&apos;s sleeping-robe, with waist and drawers combined.&rdquo; It reaches from the neck to the feet and is of white, bleached muslim, and untrimmed. Everyone who received the <mark>Endowments</mark>, a peculiar series of ceremonies initiating the Mormons into the inner mysteries, wears this. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 391</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
